data-triple-N3.o: "The Legion of Honour, or in full the National Order of the Legion of Honour (French: Ordre national de la Legion d'honneur) is a French order established by Napoleon Bonaparte on 19 May 1802. The Order is the highest decoration in France and is divided into five degrees: Chevalier (Knight), Officier (Officer), Commandeur (Commander), Grand Officier (Grand Officer) and Grand Croix (Grand Cross)."@en
